Class SortedArrayList<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractCollection<E>

  • Type Parameters:
    E -
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Iterable<E>, java.util.Collection<E>, java.util.List<E>, java.util.RandomAccess

    public class SortedArrayList<E>
extends java.util.ArrayList<E>
    A constantly sorted ArrayList. Elements are added in place and indexOf uses a binary search. addSorted is used in place of add in order to keep contract with List.
    Version:
    1.0.0 rev0
    Author:
    nfischer3

      • indexOf

        public int indexOf(java.lang.Object o)
        returns the index where the object can be found
        Specified by:
        indexOf in interface java.util.List<E>
        Overrides:
        indexOf in class java.util.ArrayList<E>
        Parameters:
        o - element to search for
        Returns:
        the index of the search key, if it is contained in the list; otherwise, (-(insertion point) - 1). The insertion point is defined as the point at which the key would be inserted into the list: the index of the first element greater than the key, or list.size() if all elements in the list are less than the specified key. Note that this guarantees that the return value will be >= 0 if and only if the key is found.
        See Also:
        ArrayList.indexOf(java.lang.Object)
